OL,3,CToxic legacy: Why is Britain behind
OL,4,CEurope in tackling DES scandal?
OL,6,FSocial Affairs Correspondent Sarah
OL,7,FCorker travels to the Netherlands with
OL,8,Fthe Tonight programme to find out more
OL,9,Fabout the country's handling of the
OL,10,FDES drug scandal and if Britain should
OL,11,Ffollow suit
OL,13,FA drug once hailed as a medical
OL,14,Fbreakthrough is now at the centre of
OL,15,Fone of Britain's most disturbing
OL,16,Fhealth scandals, and its legacy is
OL,17,Fstill being felt three generations on.
