OL,3,CToxic legacy: Why is Britain behind
OL,4,CEurope in tackling DES scandal?
OL,6,FHow the UK health authorities and
OL,7,Fregulators, past and present, have
OL,8,Fhandled the human tragedy of
OL,9,FDiethylstilbestrol (DES) contrasts
OL,10,Fstarkly with other countries in Europe.
OL,12,FITV's Tonight programme has been
OL,13,Finvestigating the use of DES, also
OL,14,Fknown as Stilboestrol, a synthetic
OL,15,Foestrogen prescribed to thousands of
OL,16,Fpregnant women through the NHS between
OL,17,Fthe 1940s and 1980s.
