OL,3,CToxic legacy: Why is Britain behind
OL,4,CEurope in tackling DES scandal?
OL,6,FChristine Holt, 71, from Worcester,
OL,7,Fwas exposed to DES in her mother's
OL,8,Fwomb and has had lifelong reproductive
OL,9,Fhealth problems.
OL,11,FShe said the UK government had "done
OL,12,Fnothing" and "didn't want to know"
OL,13,Fabout how women had suffered. "It's
OL,14,Fbeen frustrating, especially knowing
OL,15,Fthat it's recognised in other
OL,16,Fcountries, but not here," she added.
