OL,6,FHowever, in 1992, there was a huge
OL,7,Fbreakthrough when the Dutch Supreme
OL,8,FCourt ruled that this proof was not
OL,9,Fnecessary, following similar legal
OL,10,Fcases in the United States where the
OL,11,Fburden of proof was reversed.
OL,13,FInstead, the manufacturer had to prove
OL,14,Fthey had not supplied the drug. The
OL,15,Fcourt ruled that any manufacturer
OL,16,Fplacing a product on the market at
OL,17,Fthat time would be jointly and
OL,18,Fseverally liable for the whole damage.
