OL,6,FTo avoid further lengthy legal
OL,7,Fproceedings, a settlement was agreed
OL,8,Fbetween victims and the pharmaceutical
OL,9,Fcompanies and insurers, resulting in a
OL,10,FE38 million compensation fund for DES
OL,11,Fmothers, daughters, sons and even some
OL,12,Fgrandchildren.
OL,14,FA new law even had to be created in
OL,15,F2005 to declare the settlement
OL,16,Fgenerally binding.
